)	Individual Initiative: Employee’s willingness and motivation to be part of the company and culture. IDEO individuals are highly engaged and vocal within the company. 
2)	Competitiveness: The level of which competition exists among groups: it can be healthy or unhealthy. IDEO’s competitiveness amongst teams is healthy because they still support and lift each other up.
3)	Propensity for Risk: How much is risk-taking tolerated and promoted amongst employees. Because of the creative nature of IDEO’s work, there is a high motivation of risk taking.
4)	Power distance: What is the distance in terms of authority and decision making between employees and leadership. IDEO’s team-based structure makes the power distance almost nonexistent.



